      <div class="seo-concept-faq-list reveal">
        <details class="seo-concept-faq-item" open>
          <summary>What are AIO optimization services?</summary>
          <p>AIO optimization services improve how your pages are structured, understood, and trusted across modern search experiences, including AI summaries, answer-focused results, and commercial search journeys. The work usually includes page restructuring, entity clarification, schema direction, answer blocks, and conversion improvements.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="seo-concept-faq-item">
          <summary>Is AIO different from SEO?</summary>
          <p>Yes, but the two should work together. SEO helps pages rank and earn search visibility, while AIO focuses more on clarity, extractability, trust signals, and answer readiness so content performs better in AI-influenced search experiences too.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="seo-concept-faq-item">
          <summary>Which pages benefit most from AIO optimization?</summary>
          <p>Service pages, solution pages, comparison pages, high-intent landing pages, and supporting FAQ or blog content usually benefit the most because these pages directly shape how people discover, understand, and act on your offer.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="seo-concept-faq-item">
          <summary>Do you help with schema and entity signals?</summary>
          <p>Yes. We review how your brand, services, topics, and page relationships are presented, then improve supporting schema and content context so the site communicates those signals more clearly.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="seo-concept-faq-item">
          <summary>How do you measure AIO performance?</summary>
          <p>We look at page engagement, search visibility movement, consultation actions, supporting query performance, content quality improvements, and the business outcomes tied to the pages we optimize. Reporting stays focused on useful signals, not vanity metrics alone.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="seo-concept-faq-item">
          <summary>Can AIO optimization work with our existing SEO strategy?</summary>
          <p>Absolutely. In most cases AIO works best as an extension of strong SEO, content, and CRO foundations. We use what already exists, improve weak sections, and make the site more useful for both users and modern search systems.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
